- [http://www.ifac-control.org/awards/ifac-fellows International Federation of Automatic Control (IFAC) Fellow], 2016
- TEES Distinguished Research Professor, 2015
- [http://tamest.org/members-and-affiliates/members The Academy of Medicine, Engineering, & Science of Texas (TAMEST) Member], 2015
- TIAS Faculty Fellow, Texas A&M University, 2014
- Member Thomas Green Clemson Academy of Engineering, 2014
- Member National Academy of Engineering, 2012
- Alexander von Humboldt Foundation Research Award, 2011
- NASA Appreciation Award for service to the Hubble repair missions, 2005 
- The American Astronautical Society (AAS) Fellow, 2005
- Distinguished Engineer Award, University Alabama Huntsville, 2003
- Director Aerospace Program (interdepartmental program), UCSD, 2000-02
- AIAA Student Chapter Advisor, 2000-02
- Distinguished Lecturer Award, University of Maryland, 1999
- Norman Medal, American Society of Civil Engineers, 1999
- Member, External Independent Readiness Review Committee, Second and Third Servicing Mission for the Hubble Space Telescope, 1997-99
- Fellow, Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers (IEEE), 1995
- Humboldt Senior U.S- Scientist Award, Alexander von Humboldt Foundation, 1991
- Certificate of Appreciation, NASA Control-Structures Interaction, Guest Investigator Program, 1991
- Russell Severance Springer Chair, University of California Berkeley, 1991
- Fellow, American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics (AIAA), 1990
- Vice Chairman of Applications Technical Committee, International Federation of Automatic Control (IFAC), 1989-94
- Japan Society for the Promotion of Science Award, 1986
- National Research Council ad hoc committee on NASA-Universities Relationships in Aero/Space Engineering, 1984-85
- Member, National Research Council's Aeronautics and Space Engineering Board (ASEB), 1983-88
- Member Educational Policy Committee, Purdue University, 1983-86
- Member University Senate, Purdue University, 1983-86
- Jane's Who's Who in Aviation and Aerospace, U.S- Edition, 1981
- SKYLAB Achievement Award from James Fletcher, Administrator, NASA, 1974
- ORBIT Award, Sperry Rand Corp, 1970
- Walter Merit Riggs Award, Clemson University, 1963
- Who's Who Among Students in American Colleges and Universities, 1963
- W.F- Poole Alumni Scholarship, Clemson University, 1962-63
- Clemson Engineering Foundation Scholarship, 1961-62
- Certificate of Appreciation for Excellence in Teaching, United States Marine Corps, 1960
